race.comment: LUTON HOO (5) resumes here but has a handy fresh record with a win and a placing from three first-up attempts and has revved up for this with a recent trial placing here. Gets the services of Thompson in the irons from the favourable draw and should take some running down. BIG BOY GEORGE (1) is a four-time winner over this six-furlong journey and gets a stack of weight relief with the 3kg claim. Has a bit of class on this line-up. CAXTON LASS (12) is a last-start winner who is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Top-three commodity. CRACKENTHORPE (4) saves his best form for his home circuit here yet to miss a place in five outings. Do not dismiss lightly.
